\subsection*{Class interfaces}

Class interfaces are inferred from class definitions. 
They may also be defined directly in interfaces of modules. 
For instance, the following is the interface of a module defining
class "restricted_point".
\begin{caml_example}
class type restricted_point_type = 
  object 
    val mutable x : int
    method get_x : int
    method private move : int -> unit
    method bump : unit
end;;
class restricted_point' = (restricted_point : int -> restricted_point_type);;
class restricted_point' x = (restricted_point x : restricted_point_type);;

module type POINT = sig 
  class restricted_point' : int ->
    object    
      val mutable x : int
      method get_x : int
      method private move : int -> unit
      method bump : unit
    end 
end;;
module Point : POINT = struct 
  class restricted_point' = restricted_point
end;;
\end{caml_example}

