It is sometime necessary to restrict the interface of classes.
Instance variables and protected methods can be hidden by signature
matching, as shown below. However, public methods cannot be hidden.
\begin{caml_example}
module type ABSPOINT = sig 
  class restricted_point' : int -> 
    object 
      method get_x : int
      method bump : unit
    end 
end;;
module Abspoint : ABSPOINT = Point;;
\end{caml_example}

